Method Detail

getBaseModel

public final OWLOntologyImpl getBaseModel()
Description copied from interface: OWLModel
Get the model where the changes will be made (create and add) by default. (Note that set and remove methods invoked on this model my cause updates throughout the entire model, i.e., also in sub models of this model.)

If this model is a KB then it is the base ontology of the KB. At the creation time of each KB an empty ontology is created to be the base ontology of the KB. All createXXX and addXXX methods will actually modify this base ontology. However, removeXXX and setXXX methods may modify any sub ontology in the KB, provided that it is not in read-only mode.

If this model is a ontology then the base model is the ontology not containing the statements of its imported ontologies (if any).

Specified by:
getBaseModel in interface OWLModel
Returns:
The base model.

public java.util.Set<OWLOntology> getOntologies(boolean all)
Description copied from interface: OWLKnowledgeBase
Return the set of ontologies loaded to this KB with the option to include/exclude imported ones. An ontology ont is considered to be imported if there was no explicit method call to load the ontology, i.e, OWLKnowledgeBase.load(OWLOntology, boolean) or OWLKnowledgeBase.read(URI), but ont was imported by one of the loaded ontologies.

load

public OWLOntologyImpl load(OWLOntology ont,
                            boolean withImports)
Description copied from interface: OWLKnowledgeBase
Load the ontology to the KB. If the ontology is created using another KB a copy will be created before load. The imports will automatically be loaded if the second parameter is true. It is guaranteed that OWLOntology.getKB() on the returned OWLOntology (and any of its import ontologies) will return a reference to this KB.

The ontology will be rejected if it causes this KB to become inconsistent. This requires a reasoner to be attached to this KB (see OWLKnowledgeBase.getReasoner()) and auto consistency to be active (see OWLKnowledgeBase.isAutoConsistency()).

Specified by:
load in interface OWLKnowledgeBase
Parameters:
ont - The ontology to load or null if it was not loaded.
withImports - Whether or not to include imported ontologies.
Returns:
The loaded ontology.

unload

public void unload(java.net.URI uri)
Description copied from interface: OWLKnowledgeBase
Unload the ontology from the KB. The imports of the ontology will automatically be unloaded if there are no other ontologies importing them. Note that ontologies loaded explicitly using OWLKnowledgeBase.load(OWLOntology, boolean) will not be unloaded. This method does nothing if the ontology is not loaded in this KB.

Specified by:
unload in interface OWLKnowledgeBase

readService

public Service readService(java.net.URI uri)
                    throws java.io.IOException
Description copied from interface: OWLKnowledgeBase
Convenience method to read an ontology into this KB from the given physical URI and to query for a OWL-S service individual. More precisely, the method searches the ontology resource for a service individual whose URI partially matches the given URI. For instance, if the given URI would be http://mydomain/foo.owl and the ontology contains a service http://mydomain/foo.owl#MyService the method would return this service because both URIs partially match (except for the fragment). If several instances exist it picks one arbitrarily.

This method delegates to the corresponding method of the associated reader.

Specified by:
readService in interface OWLKnowledgeBase
Throws:
java.io.IOException
See Also:
OWLReader.read(URI)

removeAll

protected void removeAll(Resource s,
                         Property p,
                         RDFNode o)
Description copied from class: OWLModelImpl
Implementations need to remove all triples. A value of null for one or more parameter is to be interpreted as the wildcard. For instance, (s, p, null) means to remove *all* objects of the subject s with property p.

Specified by:
removeAll in class OWLModelImpl
